stimulusHtml: Which of the following best describes the behavior of the code segment?

features.html:
In the following code segment,  n  is a properly declared and initialized  int  variable.

 

boolean result = false;
if (n >= 10)
{
   result = true;
}
if (n <= 50)
{
   result = true;
}
System.out.println(result);

choicesHtml: It prints  true  for all possible values of  n.
It prints  false  for all possible values of  n.
It prints  true  if  n  is between  10  and  50,  inclusive, and prints  false  otherwise.
It prints  false  if  n  is between  10  and  50,  inclusive, and prints  true  otherwise.
